### Code Quality
- Use lint rules with flutter_lints (or the project's configured linter)
- Keep functions small and focused (under 30 lines when practical)
- Apply SOLID principles throughout the codebase
- Use meaningful naming for classes, methods, and variables
- Document public APIs and complex logic with short usage comments and examples
- Implement proper null safety
- Use value objects for domain-specific types when they clarify intent
